      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Toronto Maple Leafs' latest chapter slammed shut with a whimper - 32-36-14, eighth in the Atlantic, a brutal 31 games back and a seven-game skid that buried any faint playoff hopes under an avalanche of mediocrity. <strong>Yesterday's stunning firing of head coach Sheldon Keefe</strong> - after four straight seasons without a second-round win - ignited the inevitable housecleaning, with GM Brad Treliving now holding the torch to torch the status quo. The core four - Mitch Marner, Auston Matthews, William Nylander, John Tavares - racked up points but couldn't drag this roster past its defensive black hole or goaltending roulette; 78 points won't cut it in a division stacked with beasts. Injuries to Morgan Rielly and Max Domi lingered too long, exposing depth issues that no amount of star power could patch. Now comes the real hockey: free agency looms with cap hell, the draft lottery beckons at 15th seed for a shot at top prospects like the Marlies' Fraser Minten who's tearing it up in the AHL playoffs, and whispers of a franchise pivot grow louder. <strong>Watch Treliving's first splashy trade by May 1 - </strong> it could redefine this eternal also-ran or doom another summer to irrelevance.",
        "updated": "Updated April 21, 2026"
      },
