      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Vladimir Guerrero Jr. is awakening from his early-season slumber, torching Angels pitching with three hits including a 430-foot bomb that flipped the script on a tight ballgame. <strong>The Jays' 5-2 takedown of L.A. last night</strong> - capped by Dylan Cease's 12 whiffs in five frames - snapped their skid and bumped them to 9-13, still lurking fourth in the AL East, 4 games back with a fresh two-game streak breathing life into a sputtering start. No major injuries biting them now, but the real spark is Vladdy's bat heating up alongside that Arizona explosion where Nathan Lukes raked seven hits over three days - proof this lineup can erupt when it clicks. They're not contenders yet, but wins like this stem the bleed. <strong>Tonight's rubber match at Angel Stadium</strong> looms large at 8:38 ET - win it, and they steal a series on the coast, planting seeds for a climb; drop it, and the East's wolves close in fast.",
        "updated": "Updated April 21, 2026"
