      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft room hums with that familiar pre-war tension in Ashburn - Commanders holding the <strong>No. 7 pick</strong> after a grinding 5-12 slog that landed them third in the NFC East, six games back, their lone win streak a faint echo from January. Mock drafts swarm like scouts at a pro day: Conor Orr tabs Ohio State's Carnell Tate to juice Jayden Daniels' arsenal, replacing the fading Terry McLaurin at 31; Eric Edholm eyes LSU corner Mansoor Delane, a D.C. kid polishing up for Dan Quinn's secondary; CBS's R.J. White doubles down on Tate as WR1 heir. Free agency patched holes, but needs scream at corner, safety, receiver - Adam Peters covets a trade-down windfall, like CBS's Carter Bahns blueprint swapping 7 and 71 to Dallas for 12 and 20, snagging Biletnikoff winner Makai Lemon then Tennessee's Jermod McCoy. Daniels demands weapons; Quinn rebuilds the back end. <strong>With the NFL Draft exploding Thursday in Pittsburgh, watch Peters wheel and deal - those extra firsts could redefine 2026.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 21, 2026"
      },
